1
00:00:07,220 --> 00:00:11,820
♪She looks at the bright moon
hanging high above the clouds♪

2
00:00:11,860 --> 00:00:14,140
♪And I fall into the mountains♪

3
00:00:14,220 --> 00:00:16,100
♪Protect this broken world♪

4
00:00:16,180 --> 00:00:20,620
♪A faint wish♪

5
00:00:20,660 --> 00:00:23,900
♪Life is just a dream,
isn't the world so?♪

6
00:00:23,980 --> 00:00:27,620
♪Looking back,
I count the joys of my remaining years♪

7
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:31,020
♪It's difficult to see you in my dreams♪

8
00:00:31,060 --> 00:00:33,940
♪Ignoring the coldness of the world,
I still linger♪

9
00:00:33,980 --> 00:00:37,300
♪Love and hate are intertwined,
not just in the past♪

10
00:00:37,340 --> 00:00:40,900
♪The past is painful
and time goes by in a flash♪

11
00:00:40,940 --> 00:00:44,500
♪Stars fall on the mountain top again♪

12
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:48,140
♪My heart is as pure as the moon
and connected to you♪

13
00:00:54,140 --> 00:00:56,980
[No One But You]

14
00:00:56,980 --> 00:00:58,420
[Episode 19]

15
00:00:58,420 --> 00:01:01,980
[He sits upon a pile of bones,
watching over the vast lands.]

16
00:01:16,220 --> 00:01:17,580
There is something wrong with Yudie.

17
00:01:17,900 --> 00:01:18,500
[File: Yudie]
She's a spy

18
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:19,540
for the Japanese Chamber of Commerce.

19
00:01:23,860 --> 00:01:25,780
Why do you have to be accused

20
00:01:26,260 --> 00:01:27,540
while the Marshal killed these people?

21
00:01:28,060 --> 00:01:29,740
Now that I'm labeled a hideous murderer,

22
00:01:30,660 --> 00:01:31,740
it seems only fair

23
00:01:31,740 --> 00:01:33,420
to blame me

24
00:01:33,420 --> 00:01:34,940
for every crime.

25
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:44,340
Qinghuan, are you okay?

26
00:01:44,700 --> 00:01:45,180
You...

27
00:01:45,740 --> 00:01:46,420
You are...

28
00:01:47,620 --> 00:01:48,660
Die!

29
00:01:57,380 --> 00:01:59,500
Jiang Mohan has killed
so many innocents.

30
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:00,660
Everyone in the Sparks Society

31
00:02:00,660 --> 00:02:01,900
wants him dead.

32
00:02:02,220 --> 00:02:03,820
How could he be Guzhou,

33
00:02:03,820 --> 00:02:05,380
our comrade?

34
00:02:05,940 --> 00:02:06,660
No,

35
00:02:06,860 --> 00:02:07,860
this is impossible.

36
00:02:08,740 --> 00:02:10,340
Excluding all the possibilities,

37
00:02:10,580 --> 00:02:13,300
what seems the most impossible
might just be the truth.

38
00:02:13,540 --> 00:02:15,700
But Jiang Mohan killed Qingqiu.

39
00:02:18,100 --> 00:02:19,420
If he is Guzhou,

40
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:20,900
there must be another reason

41
00:02:21,260 --> 00:02:22,460
for Qingqiu's death.

42
00:02:22,780 --> 00:02:23,580
Why?

43
00:02:24,900 --> 00:02:27,860
Because Guzhou is someone
who walks on the edge

44
00:02:27,860 --> 00:02:29,500
and sails through rough waters.

45
00:02:34,060 --> 00:02:35,300
What's your plan?

46
00:02:36,460 --> 00:02:37,900
For the next move,

47
00:02:38,140 --> 00:02:39,100
I need to be completely sure

48
00:02:39,100 --> 00:02:40,660
about his identity.

49
00:02:41,260 --> 00:02:42,180
If it comes to it,

50
00:02:42,540 --> 00:02:43,980
I will use the emergency contact

51
00:02:43,980 --> 00:02:45,020
between Guzhou and the Society.

52
00:02:45,820 --> 00:02:46,340
Oh, right.

53
00:02:46,820 --> 00:02:47,980
The way we got information

54
00:02:47,980 --> 00:02:49,220
from the chamber president

55
00:02:49,460 --> 00:02:50,940
was too easy.

56
00:02:51,340 --> 00:02:52,540
We need to be extra careful now.

57
00:02:52,540 --> 00:02:54,060
Please let Chu Yunfan know.

58
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:05,380
Hello, Miss Chihoko.

59
00:03:06,020 --> 00:03:08,540
Mohan, to prepare for the wedding,

60
00:03:08,540 --> 00:03:09,980
I made an appointment
for the dress fitting.

61
00:03:10,820 --> 00:03:12,500
This way. Let me show you the dresses.

62
00:03:17,740 --> 00:03:18,220
Here.

63
00:03:18,780 --> 00:03:20,060
What do you think of this one?

64
00:03:20,540 --> 00:03:22,860
It's the latest style we've got.

65
00:03:23,820 --> 00:03:25,700
This one would also suit you very well.

66
00:03:25,700 --> 00:03:26,900
Let me keep looking.

67
00:04:02,140 --> 00:04:03,300
Who exactly are you?

68
00:04:09,460 --> 00:04:10,300
Mohan.

69
00:04:12,700 --> 00:04:14,300
Look. How's this one?

70
00:04:14,620 --> 00:04:15,340
It's nice.

71
00:04:16,660 --> 00:04:18,380
I'll try it on for you.

72
00:04:18,460 --> 00:04:19,060
Okay.

73
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:21,460
This way, please.

74
00:04:39,620 --> 00:04:40,180
Are you...

75
00:04:40,900 --> 00:04:42,100
Guzhou?

76
00:04:45,900 --> 00:04:46,780
What's that sound?

77
00:04:48,460 --> 00:04:50,060
Probably, someone is nailing something.

78
00:04:50,780 --> 00:04:52,140
Nailing something?

79
00:05:06,770 --> 00:05:11,700
[Merchant Group Wharf]

80
00:05:25,420 --> 00:05:28,380
Miss Chihoko, you're always meticulous
about your appearance.

81
00:05:28,620 --> 00:05:30,140
Why do you look like this today?

82
00:05:31,380 --> 00:05:32,580
I don't think

83
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:34,540
it's your place to ask.

84
00:05:35,340 --> 00:05:36,860
Remember, Yu Qinghuan,

85
00:05:37,300 --> 00:05:39,740
I'll be the lady of this mansion,

86
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:40,780
not you.

87
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:43,860
When will be your big day?

88
00:05:43,860 --> 00:05:45,700
I'll come by for a drink.

89
00:05:46,940 --> 00:05:47,820
Good.

90
00:05:48,580 --> 00:05:50,300
When I'm done with my business,

91
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:52,700
it will be an even bigger day.

92
00:06:11,180 --> 00:06:13,500
Chihoko must have been
to the port today.

93
00:06:13,740 --> 00:06:15,340
Have the munitions

94
00:06:15,740 --> 00:06:17,220
been secretly shipped in?

95
00:06:17,940 --> 00:06:19,420
Or is she bluffing?

96
00:06:43,660 --> 00:06:46,820
This outfit looks quite elegant,

97
00:06:47,380 --> 00:06:48,740
not as rich in colors as before.

98
00:06:50,260 --> 00:06:52,180
Perhaps it's a change of mindset.

99
00:06:52,580 --> 00:06:54,340
It's like when dawn breaks

100
00:06:54,340 --> 00:06:55,620
and the fog clears,

101
00:06:55,860 --> 00:06:57,300
one also feels brightened.

102
00:06:58,980 --> 00:06:59,620
Why?

103
00:07:01,700 --> 00:07:02,540
Take a guess.

104
00:07:04,260 --> 00:07:04,740
Where are you going?

105
00:07:08,140 --> 00:07:09,180
To make a qipao.

106
00:07:09,420 --> 00:07:10,220
No.

107
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:13,660
Things aren't safe out there.

108
00:07:14,620 --> 00:07:16,260
I'm busy with work

109
00:07:16,260 --> 00:07:17,460
and can't keep an eye on you.

110
00:07:20,580 --> 00:07:22,420
Do I look like I need protecting?

111
00:07:30,420 --> 00:07:31,340
Take a break.

112
00:07:32,020 --> 00:07:33,060
Without my permission,

113
00:07:33,060 --> 00:07:34,220
you're not going anywhere.

114
00:07:43,020 --> 00:07:43,620
Okay.

115
00:07:44,260 --> 00:07:45,220
Wherever you go,

116
00:07:45,860 --> 00:07:46,860
I'm going.

117
00:08:33,100 --> 00:08:35,700
Why do I feel you've been
in a good mood lately?

118
00:08:35,940 --> 00:08:36,620
Have I?

119
00:08:37,900 --> 00:08:38,900
I think so.

120
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:42,700
♪Like ears waiting for an answer♪

121
00:08:43,300 --> 00:08:49,220
♪Those who can't see clearly
still struggle♪

122
00:08:50,460 --> 00:08:54,340
♪The words once said will become scabs♪

123
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:58,420
♪Love hasn't etched itself
into gray hair♪

124
00:08:58,460 --> 00:09:03,980
♪Yet that doesn't stop me
from gazing at you♪

125
00:09:05,540 --> 00:09:11,940
♪Whose voice was crawling its way
into my dream♪

126
00:09:11,940 --> 00:09:12,940
What are you doing?

127
00:09:14,260 --> 00:09:15,420
Forget it if you don't want to.

128
00:09:15,420 --> 00:09:16,780
♪I wake up to a quiet peace♪

129
00:09:16,780 --> 00:09:20,180
♪Time tells me to let go♪

130
00:09:20,180 --> 00:09:24,140
♪I've waited for the spring rain
to evaporate in summer♪

131
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:28,340
♪And autumn leaves to decay in winter♪

132
00:09:28,380 --> 00:09:30,900
♪But I couldn't wait♪

133
00:09:30,900 --> 00:09:35,580
♪For the flowers we planted together
to bloom in all four seasons♪

134
00:09:35,620 --> 00:09:39,740
♪I've waited for the sunset to fall
over mountains and turn into dusk♪

135
00:09:40,180 --> 00:09:43,500
♪And the moon and stars to shift♪

136
00:09:43,540 --> 00:09:45,340
♪But I couldn't wait for us♪

137
00:09:45,340 --> 00:09:51,500
♪To weather the nights
and greet a fine day together♪

138
00:10:07,300 --> 00:10:14,620
♪Whose voice was crawling its way
into my dream♪

139
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:18,620
♪I wake up to a quiet peace♪

140
00:10:19,140 --> 00:10:20,540
Why are you still awake?

141
00:10:21,300 --> 00:10:22,300
What are you thinking?

142
00:10:23,260 --> 00:10:24,460
I'm thinking

143
00:10:25,220 --> 00:10:26,780
how long you can keep up the act.

144
00:10:27,340 --> 00:10:28,500
What do you mean?

145
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:29,980
♪And autumn leaves to decay in winter♪

146
00:10:30,260 --> 00:10:32,820
♪But I couldn't wait for us♪

147
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:37,740
♪To weather the nights
and greet a fine day together♪

148
00:10:56,100 --> 00:10:56,900
Sorry for making you wait.

149
00:10:56,900 --> 00:10:57,420
Have a seat.

150
00:11:01,420 --> 00:11:02,020
The information

151
00:11:02,020 --> 00:11:03,460
was indeed a trap.

152
00:11:03,820 --> 00:11:05,660
Thank you for sending me the message

153
00:11:05,660 --> 00:11:07,140
so we didn't lose all our people.

154
00:11:08,580 --> 00:11:10,140
We did lose many, though.

155
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:12,180
That means

156
00:11:12,180 --> 00:11:14,860
the chamber president and Chihoko
were just putting on a show.

157
00:11:15,780 --> 00:11:17,260
Jiang Mohan is also an accomplice.

158
00:11:17,980 --> 00:11:19,100
I will make them

159
00:11:19,420 --> 00:11:20,660
pay so much

160
00:11:20,660 --> 00:11:22,020
for this.

161
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:27,740
Take a break.

162
00:11:28,060 --> 00:11:29,180
Without my permission,

163
00:11:29,180 --> 00:11:30,460
don't go anywhere.

164
00:11:31,060 --> 00:11:32,900
The Sparks Society dodged a blow here.

165
00:11:33,820 --> 00:11:35,020
There's no more time for guessing.

166
00:11:35,420 --> 00:11:36,700
We need to recognize each other soon.

167
00:11:37,820 --> 00:11:39,940
Fan, calm down.

168
00:11:39,940 --> 00:11:40,980
Please do me a favor

169
00:11:41,260 --> 00:11:43,740
and put an advertisement
in the newspaper.

170
00:11:46,620 --> 00:11:47,420
Okay.

171
00:11:55,060 --> 00:11:56,220
We got the tip

172
00:11:56,220 --> 00:11:58,340
that Yu Qinghuan booked a room
at the Haoyun Teahouse.

173
00:11:58,340 --> 00:12:00,500
She seems to be meeting
someone important.

174
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:05,060
Make sure to get a bug in there.

175
00:12:05,060 --> 00:12:06,860
Find out what they're up to.

176
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:07,780
Yes, Miss.

177
00:12:16,100 --> 00:12:18,870
[Missing Person]

178
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:02,220
♪The waves♪

179
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:06,500
♪When will you stop
looking through them?♪

180
00:13:06,580 --> 00:13:10,540
♪Missed the time
when the sun was restored♪

181
00:13:10,620 --> 00:13:14,700
♪What else do you expect to like?♪

182
00:13:14,740 --> 00:13:17,460
♪I thought you were an angel♪

183
00:13:17,540 --> 00:13:19,740
♪An angel who watched over me♪

184
00:13:19,780 --> 00:13:22,820
♪And saw every side of me♪

185
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:25,460
♪Until reality is flooded♪

186
00:13:25,540 --> 00:13:27,700
♪You become sensible♪

187
00:13:27,780 --> 00:13:32,260
♪You are finally
out of touch with reality♪

188
00:13:32,580 --> 00:13:35,100
♪I hear the mountains, the seas,
and the people♪

189
00:13:35,180 --> 00:13:37,140
♪All clamoring because of you♪

190
00:13:37,260 --> 00:13:39,220
♪Hiding in the cape after the rain♪

191
00:13:39,380 --> 00:13:41,660
♪I cannot hear you♪

192
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:45,180
♪So I opened my arms one last time♪

193
00:13:45,340 --> 00:13:48,700
♪But you escaped through the gap♪

194
00:13:48,820 --> 00:13:51,020
♪I saw winters come and summers go♪

195
00:13:51,060 --> 00:13:53,180
♪And thought there was ample time♪

196
00:13:53,420 --> 00:13:55,220
♪Cannot withstand the waves♪

197
00:13:55,340 --> 00:13:57,300
♪But you always make me panic♪

198
00:13:57,380 --> 00:14:01,620
♪How ridiculous, making me learn♪

199
00:14:01,700 --> 00:14:04,980
♪How much I am worth♪
